title: 'Afraid to dream': Ireland struggles with expectation as Rugby World Cup kicks off
description: It's time for the world's keenest underdogs to finally tackle the burden of being a favourite.

title: That 70's Show actor given 30 years to life in prison for raping two women
description: Actor Danny Masterson has been given a jail sentence of 30 years to life for raping two women 20 years ago.

title: Seriously ill man trapped in cave appears in new video 3,000ft underground
description: A trapped caver awaiting rescue after becoming seriously ill more than 3,000ft underground has appeared in a new video saying he had been "close to the edge" before the arrival of vital medical supplies.

title: Thousands disqualified for 'cheating' in marathon
description: Thousands of runners have been disqualified from Mexico's most popular marathon after accusations of mass cheating.

title: Suspected people smuggler tells court he's made mistakes but 'I am not a boss'
description: Hewa Rahimpur, a London shopkeeper charged with being an international people smuggler, has told a Belgian court that "I am guilty, I have made mistakes but I am not a boss".

title: Niece of late J-pop mogul cries as she apologises and steps down over sexual abuse scandal
description: The niece of a powerful Japanese pop mogul found to have sexually abused hundreds of young performers has publicly apologised and stepped down from running the talent agency he founded.

title: Warning over hurricane with 150mph winds set to hit Caribbean
description: Tropical Storm Lee has strengthened into a category 1 hurricane - and could become "extremely dangerous" over the weekend as it heads towards islands in the Caribbean.

title: Ryanair boss Michael O'Leary laughs while being pied in the face
description: Ryanair boss Michael O'Leary has been hit in the face with cream pies by environmental protesters.

title: Race to rescue seriously ill man trapped in cave thousands of feet underground
description: A major rescue operation to reach a caver trapped thousands of feet underground after becoming seriously ill on an exploration mission will be "difficult" and could take days, experts have warned.

title: 'One player is going to die': Tennis star's shock outburst as he plays final in scorching conditions
description: Scorching temperatures at the US Open have sparked a shock courtside outburst from Russian champion Daniil Medvedev.

title: 'Glittering gold blob' found on sea floor baffles scientists
description: A mysterious golden orb found on the sea floor has baffled scientists.

title: 'World's most expensive coin' unveiled in honour of Queen Elizabeth II
description: Made with almost 4kg of gold and more than 6,426 diamonds, a new coin has been unveiled in honour of the late Queen - and may be among the most valuable of all time.

title: Mexico decriminalises abortion nationwide
description: Mexico's Supreme Court has decriminalised abortion nationwide.

title: Police in Pakistan raid at least 20 homes in search for Sara Sharif's family
description: Police in Pakistan have raided at least 20 homes nationwide as they search for Sara Sharif's family, Sky News understands.
